    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into fries</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-cheeseburger-with-sweet-potato-fries/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until crisp and golden</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-cheeseburger-with-sweet-potato-fries/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> thinly</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-cheeseburger-with-sweet-potato-fries/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash then remove <strong>leaves</strong> (1 per person!) from your <strong>lettuce</strong>, pat it dry with kitchen paper and set aside</p><p>Chop the <strong>inner core</strong> into quarters, lengthways</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-cheeseburger-with-sweet-potato-fries/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>meat-free patty[ies]</strong>, press them down firmly with a spatula and cook for 5 min on one side or until lightly charred</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-cheeseburger-with-sweet-potato-fries/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once lightly charred, flip the patty[ies] and increase the heat to medium-high and cook for a further 3 min or until browned on both sides</p><p>Top with the <strong>sliced cheese</strong> and your <strong>smoked sea salt flakes</strong>, cover with a lid and cook for a final 2 min or until the cheese has melted and the burger[s] is cooked through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-cheeseburger-with-sweet-potato-fries/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half (if required!)</p><p>When the fries are almost cooked, add the <strong>brioche halves</strong> to the baking tray[s], cut side up, on top of the fries and return to the oven for 4-5 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-cheeseburger-with-sweet-potato-fries/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To build your burger, top each <strong>warmed brioche base </strong>with a <strong>lettuce leaf</strong>, <strong>cheesy patty</strong>, your<strong> tomato ketchup</strong>,<strong> mayo </strong>and a <strong>warmed brioche lid </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>pork & beef cheeseburger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>pork & beef cheeseburger</strong> with the <strong>fries</strong> and <strong>lettuce wedges</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>lettuce </strong>with a little <strong>olive oil </strong>and season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
